2.1 BigDecimal Class in Java

* The BigDecimal class provides operations on double numbers for arithmetic,
  scale handling, rounding, comparison, format conversion and hashing.

-> It can handle very large and very small floating point numbers with great precision
   but compensating with the time complexity a bit.

* Examples:

Input : double a=0.03;
        double b=0.04;
        double c=b-a;
        System.out.println(c);
Output :0.009999999999999998

Input : BigDecimal _a = new BigDecimal("0.03");
        BigDecimal _b = new BigDecimal("0.04");
        BigDecimal _c = _b.subtract(_a);
        System.out.println(_c);
Output :0.01


